#1 Resected rectal adenocarcinoma
I have reviewed all the above in-depth with Mrs. Toombs and her husband as well as my collaborating physician today.  Presently, overall, Mrs. Toombs is doing well by imaging today as we do not see any evidence of recurrent or metastatic disease.  It would be our recommendation per our initial plan of care with Dr. Claude to proceed with adjuvant chemotherapy in the form of FOLFOX for a total of four months, or eight cycles.  Mrs. Toombs received this locally through her medical oncologist near the Waconia area.  I have gone over the scheduled dosing of this drug as well as the common side-effects, and she has verbalized understanding.  At this point, I am not making follow-up arrangements for her, but certainly if the need arises in the future, I am more than happy to help arrange care.  Mrs. Toombs is agreeable to our plan.
#2 PAME
Mrs. Toombs is scheduled for a Port-A-Cath placement tomorrow.  She would be medically acceptable for this planned procedure.
#3 A new, mild, bilateral, pyelocaliectasis and upper caliectasis and new upper ureterectasis
I have noted that Mrs. Toombs has new-onset of pyelocaliectasis, but she is asymptomatic with a stable creatinine.  We would recommend interval follow-up without pursuing any interventions at this point.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

